news.title: Gurugram: Agencies kick off audit in 17 highrises with structural flaws, report in 45 days
news.para: DTCP had issued work orders to four structural audit agencies — Bureau Vertias, TPC Technical projects Consultants, Vintech Consultants and NNC Design International — earlier.

news.title: Ghaziabad: No basic amenities in society, Proview Infrastructure booked
news.para: According to the complainant, Kamal Kant Tyagi, the possession of flats in the society began in 2016 but the units were sold with incomplete work.

news.title: ITAT comes to rescue of taxpayer over filing error
news.para: If the investment in the new house property exceeds the price obtained on sale of the original asset, then there is no residual sum that can be subject to tax as long-term capital gains.

news.title: Mumbai: Agarwal Holdings buys Juhu property for Rs 332 crore
news.para: This is the second property bought by Agarwal Holdings in Juhu. Last year, the company had acquired a bungalow in this locality dotted with bungalows and residences of Bollywood personalities and industrialists.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM takes stock of debris disposal post Supertech twin tower demolition
news.para: ​The chief minister was apprised by the Noida Authority CEO Ritu Maheshwari that the debris is being processed at the construction and demolition waste management unit in Sector 80, according to an official statement.

news.title: Demolish 'illegal, unsafe' buildings: Shahberi residents urge Greater Noida authority
news.para: ​The group -- Justice For Shaberi Homebuyers -- has demanded that after the demolition of the illegal structures, they be given homes as per norms of the Uttar Pradesh Rehabilitation Act 2013.

news.title: SC rejects plea seeking SIT probe into transgression by builders
news.para: A bench comprising Chief Justice U U Lalit and S R Bhat told the counsel for the petitioner that they have to come with a clear case on facts and tell the authorities about any violation.

news.title: Bosch leases 2.5 lakh sq ft office space in Hyderabad
news.para: “The software major will be paying a rental of around Rs 120 per sq. ft or around Rs 30 crore annually. The lease term has a five-year lock-in period with a 9-year lease,” said three people aware of the deal.

news.title: TVS Emerald to enter Bengaluru residential market
news.para: The intended investment will see the Chennai-based company develop more than 4.9 million sq ft of residential properties in Chennai and Bengaluru.

news.title: Kolhapur administration asks land owners to give consent letters for acquisition
news.para: Even after three rounds of negotiations, the land owners from Mudshinge village, located a few kilometres from Kolhapur city, and the administration have not yet settled on the price.

news.title: Over 500 applications received by Pune development body for regularisation
news.para: The official said that the development charges for land is 0.5 % of land charges and 2% of built-up area as per the ready reckoned rates. The rates for these 566 structures were assessed and given permission for regularisation.

news.title: DB Realty may be acquired by Adani Realty: Media reports
news.para: Adani Realty, the luxury property arm of the leading multinational conglomerate Adani Group, is in advanced talks for a merger with Mumbai-based DB Realty, according to media reports.

news.title: Chhattisgarh amends rules to simplify regularization of unauthorized development
news.para: Applications for the area under the urban local bodies have to be submitted in the municipal corporation and municipalities concerned while applications outside the purview of the municipal corporation and municipality but under the planning area will have to be submitted in the town and country planning office.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh shifts its gaze to energy savings in building sector
news.para: This sector contributes to about 33% of the total electricity consumption, becoming the second largest consumer. The commercial buildings in Andhra Pradesh draw around 3,000 million units (MU) per annum.

news.title: No bricks to be sold in Ludhiana till September 17
news.para: The development might lead to crisis for the construction industry and also impact ongoing residential and commercial construction projects in the city.
